    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-09-02T00:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-09-02T00:35:00-05:00" n="639"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5767/6: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-02T09:00:00+03:25"
                            >September 2, 1943—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 10:58 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>910. Department’s 441, August 26. Both Gunter and Millspaugh approve the amended
                    wording suggested by Treasury. The latter is requesting Foreign Office to
                    telegraph instructions to Iranian Minister in Wellington [<hi rend="italic"
                        >Washington?</hi>] to proceed with discussions and is asking Government to
                    submit proposed bill to Medjliss.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
